t of the Einstein moduli space (a point for $n=3$ and a finite\ndimensional space for $n>3$), which has significant consequence for the cosmic\ntopology while restricting to the case of $n=3$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Nov 2019 06:45:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Nov 2019 08:18:27 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 25 Nov 2019 05:40:10 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 27 Feb 2020 20:53:36 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 29 Mar 2020 18:24:02 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Fri, 15 May 2020 21:29:25 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Mon, 10 Aug 2020 22:06:47 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Sat, 29 Aug 2020 06:11:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
